article.description: 5 in double figures for Davidson in 92-71 win
article.headline: 5 in double figures for Davidson in 92-71 win
article.linkText: 5 in double figures for Davidson in 92-71 win
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- Brian Sullivan scored all 19 of his points in the first half to go over 1,000 for his Davidson career and the Wildcats rolled to a 92-71 victory over George Mason on Wednesday night. Tyler Kalinoski scored 14 of his 18 points in the second half. Jordan Barham also had 18 with Jordan Watkins adding 12, Oska Michelsen 11 for the Wildcats (16-6, 7-4), who are in a two-way tie for second place in the Atlantic 10 behind four teams tied for first. Davidson was outshot 55.8 to 48.2 percent but made 12 3-pointers to one for the Patriots. George Mason had 16 turnovers to Davidson's eight. The Wildcats were 26 of 32 from the line to 12 of 26 for the Patriots (7-16, 2-9). Shevon Thompson scored 14 points and grabbed 13 rebounds for George Mason. Corey Edwards added 13 points and Isaiah Jackson and Trey Porter 12 each.
